&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 2 - Clerical Officer - 30 hours per week (Mon, Tue, Thurs, Fri- 9am to 5pm)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Emergency and Specialty Medicine CSU currently have an exciting opportunity available in our Elderly, Endocrine and Diabetes outpatient team. Duties include from reception cover and helping patients with general enquiries. We are keen to recruit energetic, reliable and self-motivated individuals who will be able to support our service in delivering outstanding patient care for patients with a life long illness who attend hospital on a regular basis. This is an excellent opportunity for someone wishing to gain experience in a large and very diverse CSU.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will be expected to work closely with the Patient Administration Team and the Clinical Team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will be expected to assist the team with delivering performance targets in the department. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for applicants who can demonstrate excellent interpersonal and communication skills with the ability to forge and maintain professional working relationships with good IT knowledge to become part of our diabetes outpatient team. An ability to learn quickly, work well in a team and a flexible approach are essential. Previous experience of working in a hospital environment or busy customer focused department would be an advantage but is not essential, as training will be provided.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information and/or to arrange an informal visit please contact:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Michelle Barrett, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Assistant Patient Services Coordinator 0113 2064937&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Gillian Box, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Assistant Business Manager 0113 2064345&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
